<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-30T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="786" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5132: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to">Cunningham</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-30T16:00:00-04:00">April 30, 1932—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>162. For the Minister. Your April 28, 9 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Your purpose, as indicated in paragraph 9 of your April 28, 9
                                p.m., has the Department’s approval provided the representatives of
                                the other participating friendly powers make similar
                                designations.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>When informed that the agreement has been signed, the Department
                                will give consideration to the question of your return to Peiping
                                mentioned in paragraph 10 of your telegram.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_CWR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>